Crescent Capital Group, LP: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 6:42 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Crescent Capital Group, LP



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Crescent Capital Group, LP is an employee owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to pooled investment vehicles, state or municipal government entities, high net worth individuals, corporations, private funds, special purpose or single investor funds, separate accounts and structured products, trusts, estates, foundations, endowments and other charitable organizations, family offices, and institutional investors including insurance companies and pension and profit sharing plans. It manages client specific portfolios and investment funds for its clients. The firm invests in alternative credit markets. It diversifies its investments across public and private credit m...
Crescent Capital Group, LP is an employee owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to pooled investment vehicles, state or municipal government entities, high net worth individuals, corporations, private funds, special purpose or single investor funds, separate accounts and structured products, trusts, estates, foundations, endowments and other charitable organizations, family offices, and institutional investors including insurance companies and pension and profit sharing plans. It manages client specific portfolios and investment funds for its clients. The firm invests in alternative credit markets. It diversifies its investments across public and private credit markets including senior bank loans, high yield debt, mezzanine debt, distressed debt securities, U.S. and European senior loans, U.S. high yield bonds, and senior secured floating rate debt obligations. It employs technical and fundamental analysis with bottom up and top-down analysis approach to make its investments. The firm combines external research with in-house research for its investments. It also specializes in special situation investments in distressed middle market companies. The firm primarily invests in the fulcrum debt tranche of underfollowed companies. Its mezzanine investments focus on leveraged acquisitions, later-stage growth financings, buyouts, recapitalizations, and refinancings and are in the form of junior debt capital and private debt securities with equity participation. The firm also provides between $5 million to $20 million of senior secured debt to private United States lower-middle-market companies, with annual EBITDA of $3 million to $15 million and enterprise values in excess of $250 million. Its target investments include cash-flow based senior secured debt, senior Term B debt, and senior unitranche debt. Crescent Capital Group, LP was founded in May, 2010 and is based in Los Angeles, California with additional offices in New York, New York and Boston, Massachusetts.
Detailed Description


